pm10: With PM2.5 being the indicator used in epidemiological studies and of interest for assessing the health impacts, no conversions to PM10 were made except in the following cases:
Conversion factors from Canada used in the previous database, by city
Standard conversion factor of 0.6  used for developed countries except for EURO

For all countries except EURO: National conversion factor if available, regional conversion factor otherwise. National conversion factor is a city population-weighted conversion factor. Regional conversion factor are not population weighted.
EURO countries : national conversion factor if available or 0.67 EURO regional mean (not population-weighted, and based on city values, not country)
No conversions were made for rural stations.
